      "content": "The logging idea makes sense, but since this is an embedded ECU, I don't have the luxury of running Valgrind or a heavy-duty heap profiler. I have limited overhead for extra telemetry. \n\nBesides just logging allocation sizes, what other systematic methods can I use to find this? Specifically, how can I track down exactly which component is failing to free its memory if the leak is happening intermittently or deep within a specific module?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
